    public class LSystemBuilderImpl
extends java.lang.Object
implements hr.fer.zemris.lsystems.LSystemBuilder
    A builder of the LSystem used to draw the structure genereted by the productions of the LSystem. For more information about lsystems please see https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/L-system.

      • configureFromText

        public hr.fer.zemris.lsystems.LSystemBuilder configureFromText​(java.lang.String[] lines)
        Configures the parameters of the LSystemBuilder from text. Valid directives are :
        • origin - used to initialise the origin of the LSystemBuilderImpl
        • angle - used to initialise the angle of the LSystemBuilderImpl, the value is scaled to [0, 360]
        • unitLength - used to initialise the unitLength of the LSystemBuilderImpl
        • unitLenghtDegreeScalar - used to initialise the unitLengthDegreeScaler in the LSystemBuilderImpl
        • command - add's a new command Valid commands are :
          • draw s - moves the turtle in the current direction of the turtle and updates the positon of the turtle
          • skip s - like draw, but doesn't leave a coloured trail behind the turtle
          • scale s - updates the effective unitLength size by multiplying by factor s
          • rotate a - rotates the direction of the turtle by a - in degrees
          • push - pushes the current TurtleState on the top of Context
          • pop - returns the last TurtleState stored in Context
          • color rrggbb - sets the color used when drawing
        • axiom - used to initialise the axiom of the LSystemBuilderImpl
        • production - defines the string replacing the symbol, must be unique for each symbol - ex. production F F+F replaces "F" with "F+F"
        Example usage :
        "origin 0.05 0.4",
        "angle 0",
        "unitLength 0.9",
        "unitLengthDegreeScaler 1.0 / 3.0",
        "",
        "command F draw 1",
        "command + rotate 60",
        "command - rotate -60",
        "",
        "axiom F",
        "",
        "production F F+F--F+F"
        Specified by:
        configureFromText in interface hr.fer.zemris.lsystems.LSystemBuilder
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - - if the arguments are not in specified format NumberFormatException if specific arguments can't be parsed to numeric values
